rors as well. I\'m translating the streaming response structure, and ensuring compatibility.\n\n\n**Parsing Gemini Responses**\n\nI\'m now integrating the parsing logic for Gemini\'s SSE format. I\'m focusing on handling potential variations in the `[DONE]` signal, adapting to Gemini\'s behavior. I am also extracting and translating the text content and finish reasons from the Gemini chunk into an OpenAI-compatible structure. I am adapting it for correct stream parsing.\n\n\n**Finalizing Gemini Output**\n\nI\'m now completing the Gemini response translation for non-streaming scenarios, incorporating both text extraction and accurate error handling, focusing on crafting OpenAI-compatible responses. I\'m focusing on handling different JSON structures. The overall functionality is working, now.\n\n\n**Optimizing Chunk Buffering**\n\nI\'m now refining the `TransformStream` to handle partial chunking from the Gemini API. I\'m focusing on managing and buffering incomplete lines. I\'m ensuring the parser extracts each complete line correctly. I\'m now making it robust for both short and long segments.\n\n\n**Refining Stream Compatibility**\n\nI\'m now adapting the TransformStream. I realize I was enqueueing strings instead of Uint8Arrays. I am adjusting the stream to encode the output of each line and send out a `Uint8Array`. I am also removing any empty data lines, as well as handling edge cases. I\'m focusing on ensuring compatibility with downstream consumers.\n\n\n**Refining Response Handling**\n\nI\'m now integrating error handling for the Gemini stream, addressing potential parsing issues and invalid JSON, ensuring the controller responds gracefully. I\'m focusing on providing more robust and accurate output parsing to accommodate a wider range of responses from the API. I\'m prioritizing overall stability and refining the data flow.\n\n\n**Consolidating Utility Functions**\n\nI\'m now integrating common logic to the relevant files for self-contained functionality. I