  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Concluding the proxy server**\n\nI\'ve successfully compiled the applet and launched the proxy server. My turn is complete. I\'m focusing now on finalizing a concise summary, highlighting the design and architecture of the proxy server.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the Resilient AI Proxy Server backend, adhering strictly to the architecture and structural constraints you outlined:\n\n- **Hono Backend Foundation**: Transformed the workspace into a standalone Node.js environment utilizing Hono and `@hono/node-server` via `tsx`, completely removing frontend artifacts for a pure API architecture.\n- **Self-Healing Cascade Core**: Built the prioritized routing engine across OpenRouter, Hugging Face, Gemini, and Fallback tiers. It incorporates the requested `AbortController` timeout logic and cleanly isolates upstream fetch failures to trigger seamless failovers.\n- **Streaming Resiliency**: Implemented the precise streaming fallback rules. The router wraps the Response body in a custom `ReadableStream` interceptor, allowing it to detect mid-flight stream interruptions. It silently cascades if the first byte hasn\'t been sent, or gracefully flushes an inline error chunk and terminates the SSE stream if data was already dispatched.\n- **Provider Adapters**: Wrote full custom adapters for HuggingFace and Gemini that correctly intercept the OpenAI `messages` array, map them to native chat prompt templates, and translate incoming provider-specific SSE token shapes back into OpenAI-compatible `chat.completion.chunk` events.\n- **Structured Observability**: Integrated structured latency and outcome logging for every request, exposing the exact tier resolution and model routing paths for observability. \n\nThe API is live and listening on `POST /v1/chat/completions`. You can preview the status and environment variable configurations by opening the app root URL in your browser."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 88606082
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
