  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Goal**\n\nI\'m focusing on dissecting the user\'s request, specifically the implied need for installation instructions. I\'ve classified this as an informational query. I\'m aiming to understand the scope - what level of detail is expected? Are we talking basic setup or a more in-depth guide?\n\n\n**Outlining the Process**\n\nI\'m now concretely drafting the installation steps. I\'ve broken it down into cloning/copying source code, installing dependencies with `npm install`, configuring the `.env` file from the example, and finally, running the server. I\'m noting the distinct dev server command (`npm run dev`) that uses `tsx` and the build/start commands.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "To install and run this proxy server in their own environment, users can follow these standard Node.js project steps. \n\nSince this was generated in AI Studio, you can export the project files directly (via the settings menu or by downloading the files) into a new directory on your local machine, and then provide these instructions to your users:\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\nRun the following command in the root directory of the project to install the required packages (Hono, TypeScript, etc.):\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\n### 2. Configure Environment Variables\nCopy the `.env.example` file to create a `.env` file:\n```bash\ncp .env.example .env\n```\nOpen the `.env` file and add the API keys for the tiers you want to enable. The proxy will automatically skip any tier that doesn\'t have an API key configured.\n\n### 3. Run the Server\n**For Local Development:**\nRun the development script, which uses `tsx` to execute the TypeScript files directly:\n```bash\nnpm run dev\n```\n\n**For Production:**\nCompile the TypeScript code to JavaScript, then start the Node server:\n```bash\nnpm run build\nnpm start\n```\n\n### 4. Connect Your Apps\nOnce running, the server listens on `http://localhost:3000` (or whichever `PORT` environment variable you set). Users can simply drop this URL into any OpenAI-compatible client. \n\nHere is an example `curl` request to test the proxy:\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3000/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \'{\n    \"model\": \"gpt-4\", \n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello!\"}],\n    \"stream\": true\n  }\'\n```\n*(Note: The proxy intentionally ignores the `\"model\"` parameter in the request and instead routes it through the prioritized cascade of free-tier models).*"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 737474961
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
