  file_change {
    absolute_path_uri: "file:///README.md"
    file_change_type: FILE_CHANGE_TYPE_CREATE
    replacement_chunks {
      replacement_content: "# Resilient AI Proxy Server\n\nA **Zero-Config, Self-Healing Free-Tier Maximizer** designed for content creators and indie hackers. It runs locally or on edge functions, aggregates free-tier AI endpoints, and automatically handles failovers silently.\n\n## How to Install (Drop-in to your repo)\n\nSince this project is designed to be lightweight and portable, you can simply copy the source code directly into your existing project or a new repository.\n\n### 1. Copy the Code\nCopy the following files and folders into your project\'s directory:\n- `src/` (contains all the proxy logic)\n- `package.json` (contains the required dependencies like `hono`)\n- `tsconfig.json`\n- `.env.example`\n\n### 2. Install Dependencies\nRun the following command to install the lightweight requirements:\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\n### 3. Configure Environment Variables\nCopy `.env.example` to a new file named `.env`:\n```bash\ncp .env.example .env\n```\nFill in the API keys for the tiers you want to enable. Tiers with missing keys are automatically and silently skipped.\n\n```env\nOPENROUTER_API_KEY=\"sk-or-...\"\nHF_API_KEY=\"hf_...\"\nGEMINI_API_KEY=\"AIza...\"\n```\n\n### 4. Run the Server\nFor development (with hot-reloading via `tsx`):\n```bash\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nFor production:\n```bash\nnpm run build\nnpm start\n```\n\n## How to Use It\n\nOnce the server is running (default is `http://localhost:3000`), you can point any standard OpenAI SDK or HTTP client to it. The proxy will completely ignore the model you request and instead cascade through your configured free-tier models.\n\n### Example using the official OpenAI SDK:\n\n```javascript\nimport OpenAI from \"openai\";\n\nconst openai = new OpenAI({\n  baseURL: \"http://localhost:3000/v1\", // Point to your local proxy\n  apiKey: \"not-needed\",                // API key is handled by the proxy\n});\n\nasync function main() {\n  const stream = await openai.chat.completions.create({\n    model: \"gpt-4\", // The proxy ignores this and uses the free tiers!\n    messages: [{ role: \"user\", content: \"Hello, who are you?\" }],\n    stream: true,\n  });\n\n  for await (const chunk of stream) {\n    process.stdout.write(chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content || \"\");\n  }\n}\n\nmain();\n```\n\n## Architecture & Self-Healing\nIf a tier fails (e.g., rate limit, timeout, 503), the proxy intercepts the error and immediately attempts the next tier in the cascade. For streaming requests, if the stream disconnects mid-flight, the proxy injects an inline error message and closes the stream gracefully to prevent client crashes.\n"
    }
