  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I completely understand. To make this perfectly suited for the open-source community as a \"drop-in\" proxy, I have just created a **`README.md`** file in the root of the project. \n\nThis README acts as the complete instruction manual for anyone visiting your repository. Here is how they will consume it:\n\n### The \"Drop-in\" Workflow for Your Users\n\nWhen people want to use your project, they just need to do the following:\n\n1. **Copy the Files**: They can simply copy the `src/` folder, `package.json`, and `tsconfig.json` directly into a new folder on their machine (or as a microservice folder inside their existing monorepo).\n2. **Run Install**: They run `npm install` to grab the tiny, lightweight dependencies (`hono`, `dotenv`).\n3. **Set Up Keys**: They duplicate `.env.example` to `.env` and drop in whichever free-tier keys they have (OpenRouter, Gemini, HuggingFace).\n4. **Start the Server**: They run `npm run dev` to start the proxy on `localhost:3000`.\n\n### Pointing their App to the Proxy\nThe README also includes a code snippet showing how developers can instantly use this by just changing the `baseURL` in their existing OpenAI SDK code:\n\n```javascript\nimport OpenAI from \"openai\";\n\nconst openai = new OpenAI({\n  baseURL: \"http://localhost:3000/v1\", // <-- Pointing to the proxy!\n  apiKey: \"not-needed\", // Handled server-side\n});\n\nconst response = await openai.chat.completions.create({\n  model: \"gpt-4o\", // Ignored by proxy, routed to free tiers\n  messages: [{ role: \"user\", content: \"Tell me a joke.\" }],\n  stream: true,\n});\n```\n\nBecause the code is cleanly separated into adapters (`src/adapters/...`), if an open-source contributor wants to add a new tier later (e.g., Anthropic free tier or Groq), they just have to copy an adapter file, add it to the list in `router.ts`, and they are good to go!\n\nIf you\'d like to export this whole project right now to put it on GitHub, you can click the **Settings icon** (top right) and select **Export to GitHub** or **Download as ZIP**."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
